4: That must be the tenth time he fell!
5:
You're gonna keep at it, Gramps? Is
it okay if we bet on you falling again?
10:
I'll have you kids know that I'm still a
strapping young lad at the age of
twenty-two! Be mindful who you call
"Gramps"!
13:
As for the wager, I'm betting that I
DON'T fall again! So don't come
bawling to me later if I end up taking
all your lunch money!
16:
Talk about scary! We're nice kids
though, so we'll buy you some
candy if WE win!
18: Hooray! That's eleven wins in a row!
22:
You've been so focused on
practicing your surfing ever since
coming here, Razelt.
26:
But of course! I must remain fit in
order to protect! It's also a far better
use of my time than whiling away at
the casino!
35: But what are you REALLY thinking?
39:
As much as I'd like to partake in the
fun and games, I cannot risk the
chance of losing all my
possessions—especially not the
Lord's Aegis!
43:
Except you just lost to those kids a
bunch of times...
47:
A-anyway! I need to take this
seriously, so you munchkins should
go play somewhere else!
50:
You're okay staying a loser then?
Want us to buy you some candy?
54:
I have not fallen so far from grace
as to require alms from children!
Enjoy your candy—you've earned it!
58: You are truly kind at heart, Razelt.
61:
As royalty, I consider it my duty to
ensure that the country's children
can put on carefree smiles.
64:
I can only hope my actions
contribute to that goal. Does that
make sense, Stella?
66:
Yes. I suppose that's also related to
your pride?
69: Indeed. You're starting to get it!
76: That's one of the kids from earlier...
80:
He's about to drown. He won't last
long.
90: We need to get a boat fast—
99:
Hang on tight! The Aegis and I will
be your boat!
106:
I haven't exactly fully mastered the
technique yet, but for now, I believe
our bonds should more than suffice.
109:
I trust in the both of you. Give me
your support!
129:
Sally forth, Lord's Aegis! So that we
may grant salvation to those who
seek it!
139:
Can't really call this surfing
anymore! It's something else entirely!
145:
Frightened out of your wits, are we?
Hah, this may be the ideal speed
after all!
148:
Alk, Stella, we're saving that child! I'm
counting on you two!
153:
We did it! Razelt, can you get us
back to land?
167: I'm no grampy; I'm a prince!
175:
Gah, not again! Just when things
were going so well!
179:
Might have something to do with
our support, or lack thereof.
182:
Gah, that defeats the whole
purpose! I must try again!
188:
The speed the Lord's Aegis was
going at earlier could not have been
possible with our support alone.
194:
Maybe Razelt just got into the flow
for a moment.
196:
Perhaps. But now he's awful at it
again.
202: I guess that's Razelt for ya.
216:
I've had enough for the day! Alk,
Stella, what say we go for a meal?
220: Sure. You have a place in mind?
224:
I'm feeling chilly, so any place that
serves something nice and warm
would be preferable!
228: Let's go for some red soup.
231:
Wait, Stella. What do you mean by
"red"? I must warn you I do not
handle spicy food well.
236: You'll be fine. Even kids eat the stuff.
